        "step": 4,
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Perfect! I've built your 3-LED counter circuit. Here's what you have:\n\n**Circuit layout:**\n- **3 LEDs** (red, green, blue) on pins 13, 12, and 11 respectively\n- **3 Buttons** (each controls one LED) on pins 9, 10, and 8\n- Each LED has a 220Ω current-limiting resistor\n- GND rail distribution connects all ground paths\n\n**How it works:**\nEach button toggles its corresponding LED on/off. When you press a button, the LED toggles between ON and OFF states. The sketch uses `INPUT_PULLUP` so each button pull the pin LOW when pressed, and the code detects button presses with a debounce delay to avoid false triggers."
      }
